data.name: toolTipItem8.Text
data.value:
Create a chart dashboard item and insert it into the dashboard.
The chart visualizes data in an XY-diagram allowing you to render a wide range of diagram types – from simple bar or line charts to financial Open-High-Low-Close graphs.

data.name: toolTipItem11.Text
data.value:
Create a gauge dashboard item and insert it into the dashboard.
This item displays a series of gauges. Each gauge can communicate two values – one with a needle and the other with a marker on the scale.

data.name: toolTipItem12.Text
data.value: Create a card dashboard item and insert it into the dashboard. This item displays a series of cards each illustrating the difference between two values. This difference can be expressed in an absolute or percent variation.

data.name: toolTipItem19.Text
data.value:
Create a range filter dashboard item and insert it into the dashboard.
The Range Filter allows you to apply filtering to other dashboard items. Displays a chart with selection thumbs over it that allow you to filter out values displayed along the argument axis.

data.name: toolTipItem101.Text
data.value: Limit calculated data in the resulting view. The Visible Data Filter uses the conditions you have specified to filter displayed data. It does not filter out any underlying data used in the calculations or in intermediate level aggregations, it just hides it from view.

data.name: toolTipItem232.Text
data.value: Elements are arranged in horizontal order in a row and moved to the next row(s) when the Date Filter's width is not sufficient. In a dashboard with several dashboard items laid out vertically, the Date Filter's height is set to the minimum value required to fit Date Filter elements.
